  <refnamediv>
    <refname>imsharpen</refname>
    <refpurpose>This function is used to sharpen an image.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   B = imsharpen(A)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>A:</term>
      <listitem><para> image matrix of the source image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>B :</term>
      <listitem><para> output image with it's sharpened features.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
B = imsharpen(A) returns an enhanced version of the grayscale or truecolor (RGB) input image A, where the image features, such as edges, have been sharpened.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
i = imread('lena.jpeg');
i1 = imsharpen(i);
imshow(i1);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>
</refentry>
